Description:
Amazing space and industrial edge
An iconic Collingwood warehouse conversion with its vast open interior and towering ceilings, this incredible residence delivers an impressive combination of quality, class and inner-urban practicality. An exceptional opportunity for professionals and investors alike, the home's light-filled interior boasts an extra-large upstairs master bedroom with WIR, deluxe ensuite and large decked terrace, two additional bedrooms (with robes and private balconies) and stylish central bathroom. Downstairs: enormous open-plan living and dining areas complemented by a distinctive central courtyard (with decking) and superb stone-bench kitchen with Franke cooking appliances and Bosch dishwasher. Add to this split-system heating and cooling, polished hardwood floors, full-size laundry and guest powder room (third WC), secure access from ROW, plus front courtyard with off-street parking space (remote-controlled rollerdoor). Stroll to Smith Street trams, cafes and restaurants, easy access to Victoria Park Station and Eastern Freeway. Absolutely one of a kind!

Description:
Powerhouse (circa 1888)
This superbly maintained and industrial edged warehouse apartment offers the best of city fringed living or investment. Located within the Foy and Gibson “Powerhouse” building (1888) the apartment is light filled and infused with quality appointments and a wonderful blend of indoor and outdoor living. Set out over two comfort filled levels the apartment comprises of master bedroom with BIRs and ensuite, 2nd mezzanine styled bedroom, open plan kitchen/living opening to large (covered) outdoor terrace/winter garden, 2nd powder room, 2nd living area/ study, Euro laundry and secure undercover car park . Other features include air conditioning, polished concrete flooring, caesar stone bench tops, european appliances, security entry and lift access. An unbeatable position and sought after location with immediate access to the CBD, MCG, Smith Street, Brunswick Street, transport, shopping, cafes and so much more. Agent - hockingstuart

Prominently located within walking distance of Smith and Brunswick Streets, take advantage of public transport, cosmopolitan cafes and a range of shopping destinations. Blue-chip investment or launching pad to success, this is classic inner-city living with all the lifestyle benefits.
* 1 large bedroom with BIR
* Spacious open-plan living and dining
* Gourmet kitchen with stainless steel appliances
* Luxury bathroom with oversized shower
* Spacious balcony with neighbourhood and atrium views
* European laundry
* Chic tiling, plush carpeting
* Secure basement car parking
* Reverse-cycle heating and cooling
* Intercom security
* Moments from transport, parklands, restaurants, nightlife

Description:
LIVE A LOFTIER LIFER
Trilby Smith Street offers unique loft style, split-level apartments that draw inspiration from Collingwood’s vibrant and inner-urban style of living.
Hats off to brilliant design. Your Trilby apartment is generously sized, efficiently laid out and has been created for modern day living, featuring a clever storage plan, oversized balconies and impressive views.
The Trilby interiors are chic, with the living area inspired by Collingwood itself: moody and stylish, all to ensure functionality and the latest aesthetic, and offers a range of internal finishes.
With a choice of between a classic or contemporary colour scheme, Trilby apartments feature:
Stainless steel SMEG appliances
Solid oak timber flooring
Natural wool carpets
Sophisticated track lighting
Durable scratch and stain resistant European porcelain benchtops
On-trend aged bronze tapware
Convenient and space efficient cupboard and drawers
Generous storage facilities
Convenient open shelving and functional cabinets
Share the rooftop garden with your neighbours and friends, enjoying a fully landscaped garden, outdoor kitchen facilities, Teppanyaki kitchen, dining area, sun lounges, recreational space and inspiring city views.

Description:
More Than Meets The Eye
This Victorian era residence with its humble worker's cottage origins and wider-than-average plan offers much more than first meets the eye. Spacious accommodation, generous light-filled living zones and flexibility are hallmarks of this surprising home. The current floorplan encompasses 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms (including a massive central bathroom/laundry), 2 good living zones, upstairs balcony area, industrial style kitchen and more. Additional benefits include a shared side driveway, lofty 2nd storey addition and the bonus of a rear workshop with separate 3rd bedroom or studio possibilities. The options here are extensive and offer exciting possibilities in a superb tree lined residential location.
Close to Abbotsford Convent, Dights Falls, Victoria Park and the Smith, Gertrude, Brunswick and Victoria Street inner city precincts. Agent - hocking Stuart.

Description:
Boutique brilliance with inner-city ease
A blissfully quiet and convenient Collingwood pocket sets the scene for this fully renovated first-floor sensation delivering a lifestyle of absolute quality and privacy in a block of only five. Designer interior boasts two double bedrooms (both with robes) and sleek central bathroom. Add to this a state of the art gourmet stone-bench kitchen with breakfast bar and all-Smeg appliances, light-filled open living/dining area leading out to a private entertainers' terrace. Other stand-out features include commercial-grade ducted heating/cooling, polished hardwood floors, double blinds and LED lighting, plus private entry, lockable storage cupboard and undercover parking space via electric-gated driveway. Serene, secure and brilliantly positioned, it's close to cafes and restaurants, freeway access, trams and trains to the CBD.

Description:
A true New York loft experience
Located in vibrant Oxford St, the warehouse capital of Melbourne, this stunning split level Edgard Pirrota designed warehouse loft has remained true to its NYC inspirations. A simple two level layout allows for light and lofty warehouse living blended with original features as well as modern appointment. Simply put everything you would expect from a contemporary residence! Comprises huge open plan living and delightful courtyard terrace, large kitchen area, separate laundry and downstairs powder room with upstairs accommodation by way of super-sized master bedroom with WIR's and ensuite, good sized second bedroom and purpose built study area. Other stand-out features include off street parking, security entry, hydronic heating, split system AC in bedrooms & living and data/av/tv/foxtel cabling. Moments from Gertrude, Smith & Brunswick Streets with easy CBD and public transport access close by.
